	<div class="tm-article-content uk-position-relative  tm-article-date-true">

				<div class="tm-article-date uk-text-center">
		    <span class="tm-article-date-day">21</span><span class="tm-article-date-month">Jul</span>		</div>
		


		<h1 class="uk-article-title">
					Irene – Profile			</h1>
	
	

		<p class="uk-article-meta">

		
	</p>
	

	
		<div>
		
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><em>Irene just arrived in China for an exciting internship in hospitality management in a 5-Star Hotel in Taizhou. She gave us her first impressions on China and her expectations on this great new opportunity she managed to get with our help!</em></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Name: Irene</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">From: Barcelona, Spain</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Age: 23</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Study Background: Bachelor in Tourism</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">University: Universitat Aut&ograve;noma de Barcelona</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">&nbsp;<img src="images/Untitled.jpg" alt="Untitled" /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><em>Caption: Irene on her first day in Shanghai!</em></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>What pushed you to seek an internship in China?</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">I was doing temporary jobs in Spain, where the job-market is currently a bit uncertain and offers little career prospect. Since the job market is a little bit precarious in Spain, I started looking for internships that could be real game-changers to me.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">I love visiting different parts of the world and learning about new cultures&hellip; I have already lived in the United States and France and I wanted to have something totally different. So China sounded like a good opportunity to me.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>What do you expect to gain from your internship in China?</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">I do not expect much really&hellip; Let me explain! I have learnt from my experiences in the United States that expectations are always going to be different from the reality encountered. I want to find out what China really is, so I&rsquo;ve decided to remain open-minded! I really hope to learn some Mandarin as well. I think it will be of much benefit.&nbsp; The experience of living and working in China is certainly going to be a real advantage in the job market whether I want to go back to Spain or stay here.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>You&rsquo;ve been here for two days now, what are your first impressions of China?</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">It&rsquo;s crowded! It&rsquo;s amazing, I thought it would have been harder to get used to it but it already feels like I have been here for one month. There are barbecues everywhere on the street, it&rsquo;s great! There are many little things that really catch my attention. All is a bit different.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><img src="images/Irene_has_new_friends.jpg" alt="Irene has new friends" /></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Captions: Irene already has new friends!</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>Did you have any difficulties so far?</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">No, I had a fantastic IntuuChina guide and the whole team has been of great help!</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>How are you finding IntuuChina services?</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Perfect! My questions were always answered quickly and I always felt supported by the team. The service I received was much more than I ever hoped. For instance, I knew that someone was going to pick me up at the airport which was great! However, I did not expect to be surprised by your team in my hotel! Thank you so much Intuuchina!</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>One word to qualify your state of mind right now?</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">&hellip; Dreaming !</span></p>
